tevenstrogatz/"><span class="byline__author uppercase kern light small">Steven Strogatz</span></a></div><p class="h6 o6 mv1 pv025"><em>July 18, 2024</em></p></div><div class="post__title__meta flex flex-wrap flex-items-start"><div class="post__title__excerpt wysiwyg p italic mb1 mt025 pr2 o4 theme__text">Common sense has been viewed as one of the hardest challenges in AI. That said, ChatGPT4 has acquired what some believe is an impressive sense of humanity. How is this possible? Listen to this week’s “The Joy of Why” with co-host Steven Strogatz.</div><div class="post__title__actions h5 mt025 flex-auto flex flex-items-center"><div class="comments-button mr05 flex flex-items-center theme__accent"><a href="#comments" class="flex flex-items-center pangram"><svg viewBox="0 0 50 50" enable-background="new 0 0 50 50"><title>Comment</title><path fill="currentColor" d="M9.4 4.2h31.2c8.6 0 9.4 7 9.4 15.6s-.7 15.6-9.4 15.6h-2.2l-.9 9.4-18.8-9.4H9.4c-8.6 0-9.4-7-9.4-15.6S.7 4.2 9.4 4.2z"></path></svg><div><span class="comments-button__count ml075 small mbold disqus-comment-count" data-disqus-identifier="139141 https://www.quantamagazine.org/?p=139141"></span></div></a></div><span class="o-divider mh075 relative"></span><div class="relative"><button class="bookmark-button mh05 flex flex-items-center theme__accent-hover" aria-expanded="false"><svg class="icon" viewBox="0 0 50 50" enable-background="new 0 0 50 50"><title>Save Article</title><path fill="currentColor" d="M2.1 0h45.8v50L25.5 37.5 2.1 50V0z"></path></svg></button><div class="q-tooltip hidden force-mobile-placement" style="width:130px;top:55px;margin-left:-65px"><div class="q-tooltip-content"><div class="q-tooltip-arrow"></div><div class="q-tooltip-inner" role="tooltip"><div class="h6t relative z1 uppercase kern--w mx025"><span class="small no-wrap">Read Later</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></section></section></div><figure class="lh-0 w-100P m-0_auto d-flex align-items-center justif